Minor setback for a Major comeback 💪🏻💯

Didn’t think this is how visiting home would end up.  I really wish I had a cooler story to tell you all but I was getting ready to go see my @nyjets play their season opening game (thank god they pulled out the victory 🙌🏻). I was taking a shower and as I was stepping out of the tub I slipped and fell, smashing my face at full speed on the edge of the bath tub.  I completely snapped my jaw in half.  I ended up having a 4 hour surgery to place a titanium plate and a few screws into my jaw.  The good news is that I didn’t have to get it wired shut.  Could’ve been much more serious injury so I’m glad it was only this. 

Fun fact: I broke the other side of my jaw in high school during football 13 years ago, leading to having my jaw wired shut for 8 weeks over the summer going into my Senior year.  Was one of the toughest scenarios I had to face but it actually taught me a lot of patience and perseverance from such an unfortunate situation.

So moral of the story you live and learn from situations like this.  I will push through this and continue to progress and not let it hinder me.  I will be on a fully liquid diet for the next 6-8 weeks and I will have to adapt my workout routines.  But this won’t stop me from staying in shape and training/motivating my clients as well as all of you that follow/support me 🙏🏻🙌🏻

Thank you everyone for the kind wishes ❤️

FASTED CARDIO 🔥💪🏻

I love to do my cardio in a fasted state first thing in the morning.  Fasted cardio is doing any cardiovascular exercise, like running, cycling, swimming, etc. on an empty stomach, typically in the morning before consuming any food.

The theory behind fasted cardio is that when you exercise in a fasted state, your body relies more on stored fat as a fuel source since glycogen (carbohydrate) stores are depleted overnight.  This can lead to increased fat burning and weight loss.

I like to drink the @onesthealth Hyperburn Fat Burner because I am able to maintain a fasted state due to its low calories. *If you are under 15kcal you are still in a fasted state.  While you are doing your cardio you will burn those 15kcal within the first few minutes. 

Here, for example, I am doing 30 sec sprints on the assault bike followed by 30 sec of rest.  I repeat this for 20-30 min.  I am always changing up what I do for cardio because just like changing variations in your workout routine, this too shocks the muscles and central nervous system.

What do you do for your cardio? 🏃🏻‍♂️🚴🏼‍♂️🏊‍♂️🏋🏻‍♀️
